4068   includeScrollOffsets: false,
4069 
4070   // must be called before calling withinIncludingScrolloffset, every time the
4071   // page is scrolled
4072   prepare: function() {
4073     this.deltaX =  window.pageXOffset
4074                 || document.documentElement.scrollLeft
4075                 || document.body.scrollLeft
4076                 || 0;
4077     this.deltaY =  window.pageYOffset
4078                 || document.documentElement.scrollTop
4079                 || document.body.scrollTop
4080                 || 0;
4081   },
4082 
4083   // caches x/y coordinate pair to use with overlap
4084   within: function(element, x, y) {
4085     if (this.includeScrollOffsets)
4086       return this.withinIncludingScrolloffsets(element, x, y);
4087     this.xcomp = x;
4088     this.ycomp = y;
4089     this.offset = Element.cumulativeOffset(element);
4090 
4091     return (y >= this.offset[1] &&
4092             y <  this.offset[1] + element.offsetHeight &&
4093             x >= this.offset[0] &&
4094             x <  this.offset[0] + element.offsetWidth);
4095   },
4096 
4097   withinIncludingScrolloffsets: function(element, x, y) {
4098     var offsetcache = Element.cumulativeScrollOffset(element);
4099 
4100     this.xcomp = x + offsetcache[0] - this.deltaX;
4101     this.ycomp = y + offsetcache[1] - this.deltaY;
4102     this.offset = Element.cumulativeOffset(element);
4103 
4104     return (this.ycomp >= this.offset[1] &&
4105             this.ycomp <  this.offset[1] + element.offsetHeight &&
4106             this.xcomp >= this.offset[0] &&
4107             this.xcomp <  this.offset[0] + element.offsetWidth);
4108   },
4109 
4110   // within must be called directly before
4111   overlap: function(mode, element) {
4112     if (!mode) return 0;
4113     if (mode == 'vertical')
4114       return ((this.offset[1] + element.offsetHeight) - this.ycomp) /
4115         element.offsetHeight;
4116     if (mode == 'horizontal')
4117       return ((this.offset[0] + element.offsetWidth) - this.xcomp) /
4118         element.offsetWidth;
4119   },
4120 
4121   // Deprecation layer -- use newer Element methods now (1.5.2).
4122 
4123   cumulativeOffset: Element.Methods.cumulativeOffset,
4124 
4125   positionedOffset: Element.Methods.positionedOffset,
4126 
4127   absolutize: function(element) {
4128     Position.prepare();
4129     return Element.absolutize(element);
4130   },
4131 
4132   relativize: function(element) {
4133     Position.prepare();
4134     return Element.relativize(element);
4135   },
4136 
4137   realOffset: Element.Methods.cumulativeScrollOffset,
4138 
4139   offsetParent: Element.Methods.getOffsetParent,
4140 
4141   page: Element.Methods.viewportOffset,
4142 
4143   clone: function(source, target, options) {
4144     options = options || { };
4145     return Element.clonePosition(target, source, options);
4146   }
4147 };

4151 if (!document.getElementsByClassName) document.getElementsByClassName = function(instanceMethods){
4152   function iter(name) {
4153     return name.blank() ? null : "[contains(concat(' ', @class, ' '), ' " + name + " ')]";
4154   }
4155 
4156   instanceMethods.getElementsByClassName = Prototype.BrowserFeatures.XPath ?
4157   function(element, className) {
4158     className = className.toString().strip();
4159     var cond = /\s/.test(className) ? $w(className).map(iter).join('') : iter(className);
4160     return cond ? document._getElementsByXPath('.//*' + cond, element) : [];
4161   } : function(element, className) {
4162     className = className.toString().strip();
4163     var elements = [], classNames = (/\s/.test(className) ? $w(className) : null);
4164     if (!classNames && !className) return elements;
4165 
4166     var nodes = $(element).getElementsByTagName('*');
4167     className = ' ' + className + ' ';
4168 
4169     for (var i = 0, child, cn; child = nodes[i]; i++) {
4170       if (child.className && (cn = ' ' + child.className + ' ') && (cn.include(className) ||
4171           (classNames && classNames.all(function(name) {
4172             return !name.toString().blank() && cn.include(' ' + name + ' ');
4173           }))))
4174         elements.push(Element.extend(child));
4175     }
4176     return elements;
4177   };
4178 
4179   return function(className, parentElement) {
4180     return $(parentElement || document.body).getElementsByClassName(className);
4181   };
4182 }(Element.Methods);

4597 n2i.animation = {
4598 	objects : {},
4599 	running : false,
4600 	latestId : 0,
4601 	get : function(element) {
4602 		element = $(element);
4603 		if (!element.n2iAnimationId) element.n2iAnimationId = this.latestId++;
4604 		if (!this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId]) {
4605 			this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId] = new n2i.animation.Item(element);
4606 		}
4607 		return this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId];
4608 	},
4609 	start : function() {
4610 		if (!this.running) {
4611 			n2i.animation.render();
4612 		}
4613 	}
4614 };
4615 
4616 n2i.animation.render = function(element) {
4617 	this.running = true;
4618 	var next = false;
4619 	var stamp = new Date().getTime();
4620 	for (id in this.objects) {
4621 		var obj = this.objects[id];
4622 		if (obj.work) {
4623 			for (var i=0; i < obj.work.length; i++) {
4624 				var work = obj.work[i];
4625 				if (work.finished) continue;
4626 				var place = (stamp-work.start)/(work.end-work.start);
4627 				if (place<0) {
4628 					next=true;
4629 					continue;
4630 				}
4631 				else if (isNaN(place)) place = 1;
4632 				else if (place>1) place=1;
4633 				else if (place<1) next=true;
4634 				var v = place;
4635 				if (work.delegate && work.delegate.ease) {
4636 					v = work.delegate.ease(v);
4637 				}
4638 				var value = null;
4639 				if (!work.css) {
4640 					obj.element[work.property] = Math.round(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
4641 				} else if (work.to.red!=null) {
4642 					var red = Math.round(work.from.red+(work.to.red-work.from.red)*v);
4643 					var green = Math.round(work.from.green+(work.to.green-work.from.green)*v);
4644 					var blue = Math.round(work.from.blue+(work.to.blue-work.from.blue)*v);
4645 					value = 'rgb('+red+','+green+','+blue+')';
4646 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
4647 				} else if (n2i.browser.msie && work.property=='opacity') {
4648 					var opacity = (work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
4649 					if (opacity==1) {
4650 						obj.element.style['filter']='';
4651 					} else {
4652 						obj.element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
4653 					}
4654 				} else {
4655 					value = new String(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v)+(work.unit!=null ? work.unit : '');
4656 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
4657 				}
4658 				if (place==1) {
4659 					work.finished = true;
4660 					if (work.delegate && work.delegate.onComplete) {
4661 						work.delegate.onComplete();
4662 					} else if (work.delegate && work.delegate.hideOnComplete) {
4663 						obj.element.style.display='none';
4664 					}
4665 				}
4666 			};
4667 		}
4668 	}
4669 	if (next) {
4670 		window.setTimeout(function() {
4671 			n2i.animation.render();
4672 		},0);
4673 	} else {
4674 		this.running = false;
4675 	}
4676 	//window.status = this.running;
4677 }

4679 n2i.animation.parseStyle = function(value) {
4680 	var parsed = {type:null,value:null,unit:null};
4681 	var match;
4682 	if (!n2i.isDefined(value)) {
4683 		return parsed;
4684 	} else if (!isNaN(value)) {
4685 		parsed.value=parseFloat(value);
4686 	} else if (match=value.match(/([\-]?[0-9\.]+)(px|pt|%)/)) {
4687 		parsed.type = 'length';
4688 		parsed.value = parseFloat(match[1]);
4689 		parsed.unit = match[2];
4690 	} else if (match=value.match(/rgb\(([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+)\)/)) {
4691 		parsed.type = 'color';
4692 		parsed.value = {
4693 			red:parseInt(match[1]),
4694 			green:parseInt(match[2]),
4695 			blue:parseInt(match[3])
4696 		};
4697 	} else {
4698 		var color = new n2i.Color(value);
4699 		if (color.ok) {
4700 			parsed.value = {
4701 				red:color.r,
4702 				green:color.g,
4703 				blue:color.b
4704 			};
4705 		}
4706 	}
4707 	return parsed;
4708 }
4709 
4710 /********************************* Item **********************************/
4711 
4712 n2i.animation.Item = function(element) {
4713 	this.element = element;
4714 	this.work = [];
4715 }
4716 
4717 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.animate = function(from,to,property,duration,delegate) {
4718 	var css = true;
4719 	if (property=='scrollLeft') {
4720 		css = false;
4721 	}
4722 	
4723 	var work = this.getWork(css ? n2i.camelize(property) : property);
4724 	work.delegate = delegate;
4725 	work.finished = false;
4726 	work.css = css;
4727 	if (from!=null) {
4728 		work.from = from;
4729 	} else if (work.css && n2i.browser.msie && property=='opacity') {
4730 		work.from = this.getIEOpacity(this.element);
4731 	} else if (work.css) {
4732 		var style = n2i.getStyle(this.element,property);
4733 		var parsedStyle = n2i.animation.parseStyle(style);
4734 		work.from = parsedStyle.value;
4735 	} else {
4736 		work.from = this.element[property];
4737 	}
4738 	if (work.css) {
4739 		var parsed = n2i.animation.parseStyle(to);
4740 		work.to = parsed.value;
4741 		work.unit = parsed.unit;
4742 	} else {
4743 		work.to = to;
4744 		work.unit = null;
4745 	}
4746 	work.start = new Date().getTime();
4747 	if (delegate && delegate.delay) work.start+=delegate.delay;
4748 	work.end = work.start+duration;
4749 	n2i.animation.start();
4750 }
4751 
4752 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.getIEOpacity = function(element) {
4753 	var filter = n2i.getStyle(element,'filter').toLowerCase();
4754 	var match;
4755 	if (match = filter.match(/opacity=([0-9]+)/)) {
4756 		return parseFloat(match[1])/100;
4757 	} else {
4758 		return 1;
4759 	}
4760 }
4761 
4762 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.getWork = function(property) {
4763 	for (var i=0; i < this.work.length; i++) {
4764 		if (this.work[i].property==property) {
4765 			return this.work[i];
4766 		}
4767 	};
4768 	var work = {property:property};
4769 	this.work[this.work.length] = work;
4770 	return work;
4771 }
4772 
4773 /************************************** Loop **********************************/
4774 
4775 n2i.animation.Loop = function(recipe) {
4776 	this.recipe = recipe;
4777 	this.position = -1;
4778 	this.running = false;
4779 }
4780 
4781 n2i.animation.Loop.prototype.next = function() {
4782 	this.position++;
4783 	if (this.position>=this.recipe.length) {
4784 		this.position = 0;
4785 	}
4786 	var item = this.recipe[this.position];
4787 	if (typeof(item)=='function') {
4788 		item();
4789 	} else if (item.element) {
4790 		n2i.ani(item.element,item.property,item.value,item.duration,{ease:item.ease});
4791 	}
4792 	var self = this;
4793 	var time = item.duration || 0;
4794 	window.setTimeout(function() {self.next()},time);
4795 }
4796 
4797 n2i.animation.Loop.prototype.start = function() {
4798 	this.running=true;
4799 	this.next();
4800 }

4962             color_string = simple_colors[key];
4963         }

4968     var color_defs = [
4969         {
4970             re: /^rgb\((\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3})\)$/,
4971             example: ['rgb(123, 234, 45)', 'rgb(255,234,245)'],
4972             process: function (bits){
4973                 return [
4974                     parseInt(bits[1]),
4975                     parseInt(bits[2]),
4976                     parseInt(bits[3])
4977                 ];
4978             }
4979         },

4981             re: /^(\w{2})(\w{2})(\w{2})$/,
4982             example: ['#00ff00', '336699'],
4983             process: function (bits){
4984                 return [
4985                     parseInt(bits[1], 16),
4986                     parseInt(bits[2], 16),
4987                     parseInt(bits[3], 16)
4988                 ];
4989             }
4990         },
4991         {
4992             re: /^(\w{1})(\w{1})(\w{1})$/,
4993             example: ['#fb0', 'f0f'],
4994             process: function (bits){
4995                 return [
4996                     parseInt(bits[1] + bits[1], 16),
4997                     parseInt(bits[2] + bits[2], 16),
4998                     parseInt(bits[3] + bits[3], 16)
4999                 ];
5000             }
5001         }
5002     ];
5003 
5004     // search through the definitions to find a match
5005     for (var i = 0; i < color_defs.length; i++) {
5006         var re = color_defs[i].re;
5007         var processor = color_defs[i].process;
5008         var bits = re.exec(color_string);
5009         if (bits) {
5010             channels = processor(bits);
5011             this.r = channels[0];
5012             this.g = channels[1];
5013             this.b = channels[2];
5014             this.ok = true;
5015         }
5016 
5017     }
5018 
5019     // validate/cleanup values
5020     this.r = (this.r < 0 || isNaN(this.r)) ? 0 : ((this.r > 255) ? 255 : this.r);
5021     this.g = (this.g < 0 || isNaN(this.g)) ? 0 : ((this.g > 255) ? 255 : this.g);
5022     this.b = (this.b < 0 || isNaN(this.b)) ? 0 : ((this.b > 255) ? 255 : this.b);
5023 
5024     // some getters
5025     this.toRGB = function () {
5026         return 'rgb(' + this.r + ', ' + this.g + ', ' + this.b + ')';
5027     }
5028     this.toHex = function () {
5029         var r = this.r.toString(16);
5030         var g = this.g.toString(16);
5031         var b = this.b.toString(16);
5032         if (r.length == 1) r = '0' + r;
5033         if (g.length == 1) g = '0' + g;
5034         if (b.length == 1) b = '0' + b;
5035         return '#' + r + g + b;
5036     }
5037 
5038 }

5040 
5041 n2i.ease = {
5042 	slowFastSlow : function(val) {
5043 		var a = 1.6;
5044 		var b = 1.4;
5045 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
5046 	},
5047 	fastSlow : function(val) {
5048 		var a = .5;
5049 		var b = .7
5050 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
5051 	},
5052 	elastic : function(t) {
5053 		return 1 - n2i.ease.elastic2(1-t);
5054 	},
5055 
5056 	elastic2 : function (t, a, p) {
5057 		if (t<=0 || t>=1) return t;
5058 		if (!p) p=0.45;
5059 		var s;
5060 		if (!a || a < 1) {
5061 			a=1;
5062 			s=p/4;
5063 		} else {
5064 			s = p/(2*Math.PI) * Math.asin (1/a);
5065 		}
5066 		return -(a*Math.pow(2,10*(t-=1)) * Math.sin( (t-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p ));
5067 	},
5068 	bounce : function(t) {
5069 		if (t < (1/2.75)) {
5070 			return 7.5625*t*t;
5071 		} else if (t < (2/2.75)) {
5072 			return (7.5625*(t-=(1.5/2.75))*t + .75);
5073 		} else if (t < (2.5/2.75)) {
5074 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.25/2.75))*t + .9375);
5075 		} else {
5076 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.625/2.75))*t + .984375);
5077 		}
5078 	},
5079 	
5080 	linear: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5081 		// summary: A linear easing function
5082 		return n;
5083 	},
5084 
5085 	quadIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5086 		return Math.pow(n, 2);
5087 	},
5088 
5089 	quadOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5090 		return n * (n-2) * -1;
5091 	},
5092 
5093 	quadInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5094 		n=n*2;
5095 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 2) / 2; }
5096 		return -1 * ((--n)*(n-2) - 1) / 2;
5097 	},
5098 
5099 	cubicIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5100 		return Math.pow(n, 3);
5101 	},
5102 
5103 	cubicOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5104 		return Math.pow(n-1, 3) + 1;
5105 	},
5106 
5107 	cubicInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5108 		n=n*2;
5109 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 3) / 2; }
5110 		n-=2;
5111 		return (Math.pow(n, 3) + 2) / 2;
5112 	},
5113 
5114 	quartIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5115 		return Math.pow(n, 4);
5116 	},
5117 
5118 	quartOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5119 		return -1 * (Math.pow(n-1, 4) - 1);
5120 	},
5121 
5122 	quartInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5123 		n=n*2;
5124 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 4) / 2; }
5125 		n-=2;
5126 		return -1/2 * (Math.pow(n, 4) - 2);
5127 	},
5128 
5129 	quintIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5130 		return Math.pow(n, 5);
5131 	},
5132 
5133 	quintOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5134 		return Math.pow(n-1, 5) + 1;
5135 	},
5136 
5137 	quintInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5138 		n=n*2;
5139 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 5) / 2; };
5140 		n-=2;
5141 		return (Math.pow(n, 5) + 2) / 2;
5142 	},
5143 
5144 	sineIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5145 		return -1 * Math.cos(n * (Math.PI/2)) + 1;
5146 	},
5147 
5148 	sineOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5149 		return Math.sin(n * (Math.PI/2));
5150 	},
5151 
5152 	sineInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5153 		return -1 * (Math.cos(Math.PI*n) - 1) / 2;
5154 	},
5155 
5156 	expoIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5157 		return (n==0) ? 0 : Math.pow(2, 10 * (n - 1));
5158 	},
5159 
5160 	expoOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5161 		return (n==1) ? 1 : (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 1);
5162 	},
5163 
5164 	expoInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5165 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
5166 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
5167 		n = n*2;
5168 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(2, 10 * (n-1)) / 2; }
5169 		--n;
5170 		return (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 2) / 2;
5171 	},
5172 
5173 	circIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5174 		return -1 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1);
5175 	},
5176 
5177 	circOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5178 		n = n-1;
5179 		return Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2));
5180 	},
5181 
5182 	circInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5183 		n = n*2;
5184 		if(n<1){ return -1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1); }
5185 		n-=2;
5186 		return 1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) + 1);
5187 	},
5188 
5189 	backIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5190 		var s = 1.70158;
5191 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s+1)*n - s);
5192 	},
5193 
5194 	backOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5195 		// summary: an easing function that pops past the range briefly, and 
5196 		// 	slowly comes back. 
5197 		n = n - 1;
5198 		var s = 1.70158;
5199 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s + 1) * n + s) + 1;
5200 	},
5201 
5202 	backInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5203 		var s = 1.70158 * 1.525;
5204 		n = n*2;
5205 		if(n < 1){ return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n - s))/2; }
5206 		n-=2;
5207 		return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n + s) + 2)/2;
5208 	},
5209 
5210 	elasticIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5211 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
5212 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
5213 		var p = .3;
5214 		var s = p/4;
5215 		n = n - 1;
5216 		return -1 * Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p);
5217 	},
5218 
5219 	elasticOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5220 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the target value, near the end of the Animation
5221 		if(n==0) return 0;
5222 		if(n==1) return 1;
5223 		var p = .3;
5224 		var s = p/4;
5225 		return Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p) + 1;
5226 	},
5227 
5228 	elasticInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5229 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the value, near the beginning and end of the Animation		
5230 		if(n==0) return 0;
5231 		n = n*2;
5232 		if(n==2) return 1;
5233 		var p = .3*1.5;
5234 		var s = p/4;
5235 		if(n<1){
5236 			n-=1;
5237 			return -.5*(Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p));
5238 		}
5239 		n-=1;
5240 		return .5*(Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p)) + 1;
5241 	},
5242 
5243 	bounceIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5244 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the beginning of an Animation
5245 		return (1 - n2i.ease.bounceOut(1-n)); // Decimal
5246 	},
5247 
5248 	bounceOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5249 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the end of an Animation
5250 		var s=7.5625;
5251 		var p=2.75;
5252 		var l; 
5253 		if(n < (1 / p)){
5254 			l = s*Math.pow(n, 2);
5255 		}else if(n < (2 / p)){
5256 			n -= (1.5 / p);
5257 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .75;
5258 		}else if(n < (2.5 / p)){
5259 			n -= (2.25 / p);
5260 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .9375;
5261 		}else{
5262 			n -= (2.625 / p);
5263 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .984375;
5264 		}
5265 		return l;
5266 	},
5267 
5268 	bounceInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
5269 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" at the beginning and end of the Animation
5270 		if(n<0.5){ return n2i.ease.bounceIn(n*2) / 2; }
5271 		return (n2i.ease.bounceOut(n*2-1) / 2) + 0.5; // Decimal
5272 	}
5273 };var WysiHat = {};

5275 WysiHat.Editor = {
5276   /**
5277    *  WysiHat.Editor.attach(textarea)
5278    *  - textarea (String | Element): an id or DOM node of the textarea that
5279    *  you want to convert to rich text.
5280    *
5281    *  Creates a new editor for the textarea.
5282    **/
5283   attach: function(textarea) {
5284     textarea = $(textarea);
5285     textarea.hide();
5286 
5287     return WysiHat.iFrame.create(textarea, function(editArea) {
5288       var document = editArea.getDocument();
5289       var window = editArea.getWindow();
5290       editArea.load();
5291 
5292       Event.observe(window, 'focus', function(event) { editArea.focus(); });
5293       Event.observe(window, 'blur', function(event) { editArea.blur(); });
5294 
5295 
5296       Event.observe(document, 'mouseup', function(event) {
5297         editArea.fire("wysihat:mouseup");
5298       });
5299 
5300       Event.observe(document, 'mousemove', function(event) {
5301         editArea.fire("wysihat:mousemove");
5302       });
5303 
5304       Event.observe(document, 'keypress', function(event) {
5305         editArea.fire("wysihat:change");
5306         editArea.fire("wysihat:keypress");
5307       });
5308 
5309       Event.observe(document, 'keyup', function(event) {
5310         editArea.fire("wysihat:change");
5311         editArea.fire("wysihat:keyup");
5312       });
5313 
5314       Event.observe(document, 'keydown', function(event) {
5315         if (event.keyCode == 86)
5316           editArea.fire("wysihat:paste");
5317       });
5318 
5319       Event.observe(window, 'paste', function(event) {
5320         editArea.fire("wysihat:paste");
5321       });
5322 
5323 
5324       editArea.observe("wysihat:change", function(event) {
5325         event.target.save();
5326       });
5327 
5328         editArea.fire("wysihat:loaded"); // HACK
5329       //editArea.focus(); HACK!
5330     });
5331   }

5454    *  - ui (Boolean): Boolean flag for showing UI. Currenty this not
5455    *  implemented by any browser. Just use false.
5456    *  - value (String): Value to pass to command
5457    *  A simple delegation method to the documents execCommand method.

5459   execCommand: function(command, ui, value) {
5460     var document = this.getDocument();

5462   },
5463 
5464   queryStateCommands: $A(['bold', 'italic', 'underline', 'strikethrough']),
5465 
5466   /**
5467    * WysiHat.Commands#queryCommandState(state) -> Boolean
5468    *  - state (String): bold, italic, underline, etc
5469    *  Determines whether the current selection has the given state.
5470    *  queryCommandState('bold') would return true if the selected text
5471    *  is bold.
5472    *
5473    * You can extend this behavior by adding a custom method to the editor
5474    * element, queryCustom(). However this API is not final.
5475    * queryCommandState('link') would call queryLink().
5476    **/
5477   queryCommandState: function(state) {
5478     var document = this.getDocument();
5479 
5480     if (this.queryStateCommands.include(state))
5481       return document.queryCommandState(state);
5482     else if ((f = this['query' + state.capitalize()]))
5483       return f.bind(this).call();
5484     else
5485       return false;
5486   }

5488 /**
5489  * mixin WysiHat.Persistence
5490  *
5491  *  Methods will be mixed into the editor element. These methods deal with
5492  *  extracting and filtering content going in and out of the editor.
5493  */
5494 WysiHat.Persistence = (function() {
5495   /**
5496    * WysiHat.Persistence#outputFilter(text) -> String
5497    *  - text (String): HTML string
5498    *
5499    *  Use to filter content coming out of the editor. By default it calls
5500    *  text.format_html_output. This method has been extract so you can override
5501    *  it and provide your own custom output filter.
5502    */
5503   function outputFilter(text) {
5504     return text.format_html_output();
5505   }
5506 
5507   /**
5508    * WysiHat.Persistence#inputFilter(text) -> String
5509    *  - text (String): HTML string
5510    *
5511    *  Use to filter content going into the editor. By default it calls
5512    *  text.format_html_input. This method has been extract so you can override
5513    *  it and provide your own custom input filter.
5514    */
5515   function inputFilter(text) {
5516     return text.format_html_input();
5517   }
5518 
5519   /**
5520    * WysiHat.Persistence#content() -> String
5521    *  Returns the editors HTML contents. The contents are first passed
5522    *  through outputFilter.
5523    *
5524    *  You can replace the generic outputFilter with your own function. The
5525    *  default behavior is to use String#format_html_output.
5526    *
5527    *  editor.outputFilter = function(text) {
5528    *    return MyUtils.format_and_santize(text);
5529    *  };
5530    **/
5531   function content() {
5532     return this.outputFilter(this.rawContent());
5533   }
5534 
5535   /**
5536    * WysiHat.Persistence#setContent(text) -> undefined
5537    *  - text (String): HTML string
5538    *
5539    *  Replaces editor's entire contents with the given HTML. The contents are
5540    *  first passed through inputFilter.
5541    *
5542    *  You can replace the generic inputFilter with your own function. The
5543    *  default behavior is to use String#format_html_input.
5544    *
5545    *  editor.inputFilter = function(text) {
5546    *    return MyUtils.format_and_santize(text);
5547    *  };
5548    **/
5549   function setContent(text) {
5550     this.setRawContent(this.inputFilter(text));
5551   }
5552 
5553   /**
5554    * WysiHat.Persistence#save() -> undefined
5555    *  Saves editors contents back out to the textarea.
5556    **/
5557   function save() {
5558     this.textarea.value = this.content();
5559   }
5560 
5561   /**
5562    * WysiHat.Persistence#load() -> undefined
5563    *  Loads textarea contents into editor.
5564    **/
5565    function load() {
5566      this.setContent(this.textarea.value);
5567   }
5568 
5569   /**
5570    * WysiHat.Persistence#reload() -> undefined
5571    *  Saves current contents and loads contents into editor.
5572    **/
5573   function reload() {
5574     this.selection.setBookmark();
5575     this.save();
5576     this.load();
5577     this.selection.moveToBookmark();
5578   }
5579 
5580   return {
5581     outputFilter: outputFilter,
5582     inputFilter:  inputFilter,
5583     content:      content,
5584     setContent:   setContent,
5585     save:         save,
5586     load:         load,
5587     reload:       reload
5588   };
5589 })();
5590 /**
5591  * mixin WysiHat.Window
5592  *
5593  *  Methods will be mixed into the editor element. These methods handle window
5594  *  events such as focus and blur events on the editor.
5595  */
5596 WysiHat.Window = (function() {
5597   /**
5598    * WysiHat.Window#getDocument() -> Document
5599    *  Cross browser method to return the iFrame's document.
5600    *  You should not need to access this directly, and this API is not final.
5601    */
5602   function getDocument() {
5603     return this.contentDocument || this.contentWindow.document;
5604   }
5605 
5606   /**
5607    * WysiHat.Window#getWindow() -> Window
5608    *  Cross browser method to return the iFrame's window.
5609    *  You should not need to access this directly, and this API is not final.
5610    */
5611   function getWindow() {
5612     if (this.contentDocument)
5613       return this.contentDocument.defaultView;
5614     else if (this.contentWindow.document)
5615       return this.contentWindow;
5616     else
5617       return null;
5618   }
5619 
5620   /**
5621    * WysiHat.Window#focus() -> undefined
5622    *  binds observers to mouseup, mousemove, keypress, and keyup on focus
5623    **/
5624   function focus() {
5625     this.getWindow().focus();
5626 
5627     if (this.hasFocus)
5628       return;
5629 
5630     this.hasFocus = true;
5631   }
5632 
5633   /**
5634    * WysiHat.Window#blur() -> undefined
5635    *  removes observers to mouseup, mousemove, keypress, and keyup on blur
5636    **/
5637   function blur() {
5638     this.hasFocus = false;
5639   }
5640 
5641   return {
5642     getDocument: getDocument,
5643     getWindow: getWindow,
5644     focus: focus,
5645     blur: blur
5646   };
5647 })();

5649 WysiHat.iFrame = {
5650   create: function(textarea, callback) {
5651     var editArea = new Element('iframe', { 'id': textarea.id + '_editor', 'class': 'editor' });
5652 
5653     Object.extend(editArea, WysiHat.Commands);
5654     Object.extend(editArea, WysiHat.Persistence);
5655     Object.extend(editArea, WysiHat.Window);
5656     Object.extend(editArea, WysiHat.iFrame.Methods);
5657 
5658     editArea.attach(textarea, callback);
5659 
5660     textarea.insert({before: editArea});
5661 
5662     return editArea;
5663   }
5664 };

5666 WysiHat.iFrame.Methods = {
5667   attach: function(element, callback) {
5668     this.textarea = element;
5669 
5670     this.observe('load', function() {
5671       function setDocumentStyles(document, styles) {
5672         if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
5673           var style = document.createStyleSheet();
5674           style.addRule("body", "border: 0");
5675           style.addRule("p", "margin: 0");
5676 
5677           $H(styles).each(function(pair) {
5678             var value = pair.first().underscore().dasherize() + ": " + pair.last();
5679             style.addRule("body", value);
5680           });
5681         } else if (Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
5682           var style = Element('style').update("p { margin: 0; }");
5683           var head = document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0];
5684           head.appendChild(style);
5685         } else {
5686           Element.setStyle(document.body, styles);
5687         }
5688       }
5689 
5690       try {
5691         var document = this.getDocument();
5692       } catch(e) { return; } // No iframe, just stop
5693 
5694       this.selection = new WysiHat.Selection(this);
5695 
5696       if (this.ready && document.designMode == 'on')
5697         return;
5698 
5699       setDocumentStyles(document, WysiHat.Editor.styles || {});
5700 
5701       document.designMode = 'on';
5702       callback(this);
5703       this.ready = true;
5704     });
5705   },
5706 
5707   rawContent: function() {
5708     var document = this.getDocument();
5709     return document.body.innerHTML;
5710   },
5711 
5712   setRawContent: function(text) {
5713     var document = this.getDocument();
5714     if (document.body)
5715       document.body.innerHTML = text;
5716   }

5718 
5719 Object.extend(String.prototype, (function() {
5720   /**
5721    * String#format_html_output() -> String
5722    *
5723    *  Cleanup browser's HTML mess!
5724    *
5725    *  There is no standard formatting among the major browsers for the rich
5726    *  text output. Safari wraps its line breaks with "div" tags, Firefox puts
5727    *  "br" tags at the end of the line, and other such as Internet Explorer
5728    *  wrap lines in "p" tags.
5729    *
5730    *  The output is a standarizes these inconsistencies and produces a clean
5731    *  result. A single return creates a line break "br" and double returns
5732    *  create a new paragraph. This is similar to how Textile and Markdown
5733    *  handle whitespace.
5734    *
5735    *  Raw browser content => String#format_html_output => Textarea
5736    **/
5737   function format_html_output() {
5738     var text = String(this);
5739     text = text.tidy_xhtml();
5740 
5741     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
5742       text = text.replace(/(<div>)+/g, "\n");
5743       text = text.replace(/(<\/div>)+/g, "");
5744 
5745       text = text.replace(/<p>\s*<\/p>/g, "");
5746 
5747       text = text.replace(/<br \/>(\n)*/g, "\n");
5748     } else if (Prototype.Browser.Gecko) {
5749       text = text.replace(/<p>/g, "");
5750       text = text.replace(/<\/p>(\n)?/g, "\n");
5751 
5752       text = text.replace(/<br \/>(\n)*/g, "\n");
5753     } else if (Prototype.Browser.IE || Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
5754       text = text.replace(/<p>( | |\s)<\/p>/g, "<p></p>");
5755 
5756       text = text.replace(/<br \/>/g, "");
5757 
5758       text = text.replace(/<p>/g, '');
5759 
5760       text = text.replace(/ /g, '');
5761 
5762       text = text.replace(/<\/p>(\n)?/g, "\n");
5763 
5764       text = text.gsub(/^<p>/, '');
5765       text = text.gsub(/<\/p>$/, '');
5766     }
5767 
5768     text = text.gsub(/<b>/, "<strong>");
5769     text = text.gsub(/<\/b>/, "</strong>");
5770 
5771     text = text.gsub(/<i>/, "<em>");
5772     text = text.gsub(/<\/i>/, "</em>");
5773 
5774     text = text.replace(/\n\n+/g, "</p>\n\n<p>");
5775 
5776     text = text.gsub(/(([^\n])(\n))(?=([^\n]))/, "#{2}<br />\n");
5777 
5778     text = '<p>' + text + '</p>';
5779 
5780     text = text.replace(/<p>\s*/g, "<p>");
5781     text = text.replace(/\s*<\/p>/g, "</p>");
5782 
5783     var element = Element("body");
5784     element.innerHTML = text;
5785 
5786     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit || Prototype.Browser.Gecko) {
5787       var replaced;
5788       do {
5789         replaced = false;
5790         element.select('span').each(function(span) {
5791           if (span.hasClassName('Apple-style-span')) {
5792             span.removeClassName('Apple-style-span');
5793             if (span.className == '')
5794               span.removeAttribute('class');
5795             replaced = true;
5796           } else if (span.getStyle('fontWeight') == 'bold') {
5797             span.setStyle({fontWeight: ''});
5798             if (span.style.length == 0)
5799               span.removeAttribute('style');
5800             span.update('<strong>' + span.innerHTML + '</strong>');
5801             replaced = true;
5802           } else if (span.getStyle('fontStyle') == 'italic') {
5803             span.setStyle({fontStyle: ''});
5804             if (span.style.length == 0)
5805               span.removeAttribute('style');
5806             span.update('<em>' + span.innerHTML + '</em>');
5807             replaced = true;
5808           } else if (span.getStyle('textDecoration') == 'underline') {
5809             span.setStyle({textDecoration: ''});
5810             if (span.style.length == 0)
5811               span.removeAttribute('style');
5812             span.update('<u>' + span.innerHTML + '</u>');
5813             replaced = true;
5814           } else if (span.attributes.length == 0) {
5815             span.replace(span.innerHTML);
5816             replaced = true;
5817           }
5818         });
5819       } while (replaced);
5820 
5821     }
5822 
5823     for (var i = 0; i < element.descendants().length; i++) {
5824       var node = element.descendants()[i];
5825       if (node.innerHTML.blank() && node.nodeName != 'BR' && node.id != 'bookmark')
5826         node.remove();
5827     }
5828 
5829     text = element.innerHTML;
5830     text = text.tidy_xhtml();
5831 
5832     text = text.replace(/<br \/>(\n)*/g, "<br />\n");
5833     text = text.replace(/<\/p>\n<p>/g, "</p>\n\n<p>");
5834 
5835     text = text.replace(/<p>\s*<\/p>/g, "");
5836 
5837     text = text.replace(/\s*$/g, "");
5838 
5839     return text;
5840   }
5841 
5842   /**
5843    * String#format_html_input() -> String
5844    *
5845    *  Prepares sane HTML for editing.
5846    *
5847    *  This function preforms the reserve function of String#format_html_output. Each
5848    *  browser has difficulty editing mix formatting conventions. This restores
5849    *  most of the original browser specific formatting tags and some other
5850    *  styling conventions.
5851    *
5852    *  Textarea => String#format_html_input => Raw content
5853   **/
5854   function format_html_input() {
5855     var text = String(this);
5856 
5857     var element = Element("body");
5858     element.innerHTML = text;
5859 
5860     if (Prototype.Browser.Gecko || Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
5861       element.select('strong').each(function(element) {
5862         element.replace('<span style="font-weight: bold;">' + element.innerHTML + '</span>');
5863       });
5864       element.select('em').each(function(element) {
5865         element.replace('<span style="font-style: italic;">' + element.innerHTML + '</span>');
5866       });
5867       element.select('u').each(function(element) {
5868         element.replace('<span style="text-decoration: underline;">' + element.innerHTML + '</span>');
5869       });
5870     }
5871 
5872     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit)
5873       element.select('span').each(function(span) {
5874         if (span.getStyle('fontWeight') == 'bold')
5875           span.addClassName('Apple-style-span');
5876 
5877         if (span.getStyle('fontStyle') == 'italic')
5878           span.addClassName('Apple-style-span');
5879 
5880         if (span.getStyle('textDecoration') == 'underline')
5881           span.addClassName('Apple-style-span');
5882       });
5883 
5884     text = element.innerHTML;
5885     text = text.tidy_xhtml();
5886 
5887     text = text.replace(/<\/p>(\n)*<p>/g, "\n\n");
5888 
5889     text = text.replace(/(\n)?<br( \/)?>(\n)?/g, "\n");
5890 
5891     text = text.replace(/^<p>/g, '');
5892     text = text.replace(/<\/p>$/g, '');
5893 
5894     if (Prototype.Browser.Gecko) {
5895       text = text.replace(/\n/g, "<br>");
5896       text = text + '<br>';
5897     } else if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
5898       text = text.replace(/\n/g, "</div><div>");
5899       text = '<div>' + text + '</div>';
5900       text = text.replace(/<div><\/div>/g, "<div><br></div>");
5901     } else if (Prototype.Browser.IE || Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
5902       text = text.replace(/\n/g, "</p>\n<p>");
5903       text = '<p>' + text + '</p>';
5904       text = text.replace(/<p><\/p>/g, "<p> </p>");
5905       text = text.replace(/(<p> <\/p>)+$/g, "");
5906     }
5907 
5908     return text;
5909   }
5910 
5911   /**
5912    * String#tidy_xhtml() -> String
5913    *
5914    *  Normalizes and tidies text into XHTML content.
5915    *   * Strips out browser line breaks, '\r'
5916    *   * Downcases tag names
5917    *   * Closes line break tags
5918    **/
5919   function tidy_xhtml() {
5920     var text = String(this);
5921 
5922     text = text.gsub(/\r\n?/, "\n");
5923 
5924     text = text.gsub(/<([A-Z]+)([^>]*)>/, function(match) {
5925       return '<' + match[1].toLowerCase() + match[2] + '>';
5926     });
5927 
5928     text = text.gsub(/<\/([A-Z]+)>/, function(match) {
5929       return '</' + match[1].toLowerCase() + '>';
5930     });
5931 
5932     text = text.replace(/<br>/g, "<br />");
5933 
5934     return text;
5935   }
5936 
5937   return {
5938     format_html_output: format_html_output,
5939     format_html_input:  format_html_input,
5940     tidy_xhtml:         tidy_xhtml
5941   };
5942 })());
5943 Object.extend(String.prototype, {
5944   /**
5945    * String#sanitize([options]) -> String
5946    * - options (Hash): Whitelist options
5947    *
5948    *  Sanitizes HTML tags and attributes. Options accepts an array of
5949    *  allowed tags and attributes.
5950    #
5951    *  "<a href='#'>Example</a>".sanitize({tags: ['a'], attributes: ['href']})
5952    **/
5953   sanitize: function(options) {
5954     return Element("div").update(this).sanitize(options).innerHTML.tidy_xhtml();
5955   }
5956 });
5957 
5958 Element.addMethods({
5959   /**
5960    * Element#sanitize([options]) -> Element
5961    * - options (Hash): Whitelist options
5962    *
5963    *  Sanitizes element tags and attributes. Options accepts an array of
5964    *  allowed tags and attributes.
5965    #
5966    *  This method is called by String#sanitize().
5967    **/
5968   sanitize: function(element, options) {
5969     element = $(element);
5970     options = $H(options);
5971     var allowed_tags = $A(options.get('tags') || []);
5972     var allowed_attributes = $A(options.get('attributes') || []);
5973     var sanitized = Element(element.nodeName);
5974 
5975     $A(element.childNodes).each(function(child) {
5976       if (child.nodeType == 1) {
5977         var children = $(child).sanitize(options).childNodes;
5978 
5979         if (allowed_tags.include(child.nodeName.toLowerCase())) {
5980           var new_child = Element(child.nodeName);
5981           allowed_attributes.each(function(attribute) {
5982             if ((value = child.readAttribute(attribute)))
5983               new_child.writeAttribute(attribute, value);
5984           });
5985           sanitized.appendChild(new_child);
5986 
5987           $A(children).each(function(grandchild) { new_child.appendChild(grandchild); });
5988         } else {
5989           $A(children).each(function(grandchild) { sanitized.appendChild(grandchild); });
5990         }
5991       } else if (child.nodeType == 3) {
5992         sanitized.appendChild(child);
5993       }
5994     });
5995     return sanitized;
5996   }

6072   /**
6073    *  new WysiHat.Selection(editor)
6074    *  - editor (WysiHat.Editor): the editor object that you want to bind to

6076   function initialize(editor) {

6081   /**
6082    * WysiHat.Selection#getSelection() -> Selection
6083    *  Get selected text.
6084    **/
6085   function getSelection() {
6086     return this.window.getSelection ? this.window.getSelection() : this.document.selection;
6087   }
6088 
6089   /**
6090    * WysiHat.Selection#getRange() -> Range
6091    *  Get range for selected text.
6092    **/
6093   function getRange() {
6094     var selection = this.getSelection();
6095 
6096     try {
6097       var range;
6098       if (selection.getRangeAt)
6099         range = selection.getRangeAt(0);
6100       else
6101         range = selection.createRange();
6102     } catch(e) { return null; }
6103 
6104     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
6105       range.setStart(selection.baseNode, selection.baseOffset);
6106       range.setEnd(selection.extentNode, selection.extentOffset);
6107     }
6108 
6109     return range;
6110   }
6111 
6112   /**
6113    * WysiHat.Selection#selectNode(node) -> undefined
6114    * - node (Element): Element or node to select
6115    **/
6116   function selectNode(node) {
6117     var selection = this.getSelection();
6118 
6119     if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
6120       var range = createRangeFromElement(this.document, node);
6121       range.select();
6122     } else if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
6123       selection.setBaseAndExtent(node, 0, node, node.innerText.length);
6124     } else if (Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
6125       range = this.document.createRange();
6126       range.selectNode(node);
6127       selection.removeAllRanges();
6128       selection.addRange(range);
6129     } else {
6130       var range = createRangeFromElement(this.document, node);
6131       selection.removeAllRanges();
6132       selection.addRange(range);
6133     }
6134   }
6135 
6136   /**
6137    * WysiHat.Selection#getNode() -> Element
6138    *  Returns selected node.
6139    **/
6140   function getNode() {
6141     var nodes = null, candidates = [], children, el;
6142     var range = this.getRange();
6143 
6144     if (!range)
6145       return null;
6146 
6147     var parent;
6148     if (range.parentElement)
6149       parent = range.parentElement();
6150     else
6151       parent = range.commonAncestorContainer;
6152 
6153     if (parent) {
6154       while (parent.nodeType != 1) parent = parent.parentNode;
6155       if (parent.nodeName.toLowerCase() != "body") {
6156         el = parent;
6157         do {
6158           el = el.parentNode;
6159           candidates[candidates.length] = el;
6160         } while (el.nodeName.toLowerCase() != "body");
6161       }
6162       children = parent.all || parent.getElementsByTagName("*");
6163       for (var j = 0; j < children.length; j++)
6164         candidates[candidates.length] = children[j];
6165       nodes = [parent];
6166       for (var ii = 0, r2; ii < candidates.length; ii++) {
6167         r2 = createRangeFromElement(this.document, candidates[ii]);
6168         if (r2 && compareRanges(range, r2))
6169           nodes[nodes.length] = candidates[ii];
6170       }
6171     }
6172 
6173     return nodes.first();
6174   }
6175 
6176   function createRangeFromElement(document, node) {
6177     if (document.body.createTextRange) {
6178       var range = document.body.createTextRange();
6179       range.moveToElementText(node);
6180     } else if (document.createRange) {
6181       var range = document.createRange();
6182       range.selectNodeContents(node);
6183     }
6184     return range;
6185   }
6186 
6187   function compareRanges(r1, r2) {
6188     if (r1.compareEndPoints) {
6189       return !(
6190         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToStart', r1) == 1 &&
6191         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToEnd', r1) == 1 &&
6192         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToEnd', r1) == 1 &&
6193         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToStart', r1) == 1
6194         ||
6195         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToStart', r1) == -1 &&
6196         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToEnd', r1) == -1 &&
6197         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToEnd', r1) == -1 &&
6198         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToStart', r1) == -1
6199       );
6200     } else if (r1.compareBoundaryPoints) {
6201       return !(
6202         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(0, r1) == 1 &&
6203         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(2, r1) == 1 &&
6204         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(1, r1) == 1 &&
6205         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(3, r1) == 1
6206         ||
6207         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(0, r1) == -1 &&
6208         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(2, r1) == -1 &&
6209         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(1, r1) == -1 &&
6210         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(3, r1) == -1
6211       );
6212     }
6213 
6214     return null;
6215   };
6216 
6217   function setBookmark() {
6218     var bookmark = this.document.getElementById('bookmark');
6219     if (bookmark)
6220       bookmark.parentNode.removeChild(bookmark);
6221 
6222     bookmark = this.document.createElement('span');
6223     bookmark.id = 'bookmark';
6224     bookmark.innerHTML = ' ';
6225 
6226     var range;
6227     if (Prototype.Browser.IE)
6228       range = new Range(this.document);
6229     else
6230       range = this.getRange();
6231     range.insertNode(bookmark);
6232   }
6233 
6234   function moveToBookmark() {
6235     var bookmark = this.document.getElementById('bookmark');
6236     if (!bookmark)
6237       return;
6238 
6239     if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
6240       var range = this.getRange();
6241       range.moveToElementText(bookmark);
6242       range.collapse();
6243       range.select();
6244     } else if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
6245       var selection = this.getSelection();
6246       selection.setBaseAndExtent(bookmark, 0, bookmark, 0);
6247     } else {
6248       var range = this.getRange();
6249       range.setStartBefore(bookmark);
6250     }
6251 
6252     bookmark.parentNode.removeChild(bookmark);
6253   }
6254

6257     getSelection:   getSelection,

6266 /**
6267  * class WysiHat.Toolbar
6268  **/
6269 WysiHat.Toolbar = Class.create((function() {
6270   /**
6271    * new WysiHat.Toolbar(editor)
6272    *  - editor (WysiHat.Editor): the editor object that you want to attach to
6273    *
6274    *  Creates a toolbar element above the editor. The WysiHat.Toolbar object
6275    *  has many helper methods to easily add buttons to the toolbar.
6276    *
6277    *  This toolbar class is not required for the Editor object to function.
6278    *  It is merely a set of helper methods to get you started and to build
6279    *  on top of.
6280    **/
6281   function initialize(editArea) {
6282     this.editArea = editArea;
6283 
6284     this.hasMouseDown = false;
6285     this.element = new Element('div', { 'class': 'editor_toolbar' });
6286 
6287     var toolbar = this;
6288     this.element.observe('mousedown', function(event) { toolbar.mouseDown(event); });
6289     this.element.observe('mouseup', function(event) { toolbar.mouseUp(event); });
6290 
6291     this.editArea.insert({before: this.element});
6292   }
6293 
6294   /**
6295    * WysiHat.Toolbar#addButtonSet(set) -> undefined
6296    *  - set (Array): The set array contains nested arrays that hold the
6297    *  button options, and handler.
6298    *
6299    *  Adds a button set to the toolbar.
6300    *
6301    *  WysiHat.Toolbar.ButtonSets.Basic is a built in button set,
6302    *  that looks like:
6303    *  [
6304    *    [{ name: 'bold', label: "Bold" }, function(editor) {
6305    *      editor.boldSelection();
6306    *    }],
6307    *    [{ name: 'underline', label: "Underline" }, function(editor) {
6308    *      editor.underlineSelection();
6309    *    }],
6310    *    [{ name: 'italic', label: "Italic" }, function(editor) {
6311    *      editor.italicSelection();
6312    *    }]
6313    *  ]
6314    **/
6315   function addButtonSet(set) {
6316     var toolbar = this;
6317     $A(set).each(function(button) {
6318       var options = button.first();
6319       var handler = button.last();
6320       toolbar.addButton(options, handler);
6321     });
6322   }
6323 
6324   /**
6325    * WysiHat.Toolbar#addButton(options, handler) -> undefined
6326    *  - options (Hash): Required options hash
6327    *  - handler (Function): Function to bind to the button
6328    *
6329    *  The options hash accepts two required keys, name and label. The label
6330    *  value is used as the link's inner text. The name value is set to the
6331    *  link's class and is used to check the button state.
6332    *
6333    *  toolbar.addButton({
6334    *    name: 'bold', label: "Bold" }, function(editor) {
6335    *      editor.boldSelection();
6336    *  });
6337    *
6338    *  Would create a link,
6339    *  "<a href='#' class='button bold'><span>Bold</span></a>"
6340    **/
6341   function addButton(options, handler) {
6342     options = $H(options);
6343     var button = Element('a', { 'class': 'button', 'href': '#' }).update('<span>' + options.get('label') + '</span>');
6344     button.addClassName(options.get('name'));
6345 
6346     this.observeButtonClick(button, handler);
6347     this.observeStateChanges(button, options.get('name'));
6348     this.element.appendChild(button);
6349   }
6350 
6351   /**
6352    * WysiHat.Toolbar#observeButtonClick(element, handler) -> undefined
6353    *  - element (String | Element): Element to bind handler to
6354    *  - handler (Function): Function to bind to the element
6355    *  fires wysihat:change
6356    *
6357    *  In addition to binding the given handler to the element, this observe
6358    *  function also sets up a few more events. When the elements onclick is
6359    *  fired, the toolbars hasMouseDown property will be set to true and
6360    *  back to false on exit.
6361    **/
6362   function observeButtonClick(element, handler) {
6363     var toolbar = this;
6364     $(element).observe('click', function(event) {
6365       toolbar.hasMouseDown = true;
6366       handler(toolbar.editArea);
6367       toolbar.editArea.fire("wysihat:change");
6368       Event.stop(event);
6369       toolbar.hasMouseDown = false;
6370     });
6371   }
6372 
6373   /**
6374    * WysiHat.Toolbar#observeStateChanges(element, command) -> undefined
6375    *  - element (String | Element): Element to receive changes
6376    *  - command (String): Name of editor command to observe
6377    *
6378    *  Adds the class "selected" to the given Element when the selected text
6379    *  matches the command.
6380    *
6381    *  toolbar.observeStateChanges(buttonElement, 'bold')
6382    *  would add the class "selected" to the buttonElement when the editor's
6383    *  selected text was bold.
6384    **/
6385   function observeStateChanges(element, command) {
6386     this.editArea.observe("wysihat:mousemove", function(event) {
6387       if (event.target.queryCommandState(command))
6388         element.addClassName('selected');
6389       else
6390         element.removeClassName('selected');
6391     });
6392   }
6393 
6394   /**
6395    * WysiHat.Toolbar#mouseDown(event) -> undefined
6396    *  - event (Event)
6397    *  This function is triggered when the user clicks their mouse down on
6398    *  the toolbar element. For now, it only updates the hasMouseDown property
6399    *  to true.
6400    **/
6401   function mouseDown(event) {
6402     this.hasMouseDown = true;
6403   }
6404 
6405   /**
6406    * WysiHat.Toolbar#mouseDown(event) -> undefined
6407    *  - event (Event)
6408    *  This function is triggered when the user releases their mouse from
6409    *  the toolbar element. It resets the hasMouseDown property back to false
6410    *  and refocuses on the editing window.
6411    **/
6412   function mouseUp(event) {
6413     this.editArea.focus();
6414     this.hasMouseDown = false;
6415   }
6416 
6417   return {
6418     initialize:          initialize,
6419     addButtonSet:        addButtonSet,
6420     addButton:           addButton,
6421     observeButtonClick:  observeButtonClick,
6422     observeStateChanges: observeStateChanges,
6423     mouseDown:           mouseDown,
6424     mouseUp:             mouseUp
6425   };
6426 })());

6485 var SWFUpload = function (settings) {
6486 	this.initSWFUpload(settings);
6487 };
6488 
6489 SWFUpload.prototype.initSWFUpload = function (settings) {
6490 	try {
6491 		this.customSettings = {};	// A container where developers can place their own settings associated with this instance.
6492 		this.settings = settings;
6493 		this.eventQueue = [];
6494 		this.movieName = "SWFUpload_" + SWFUpload.movieCount++;
6495 		this.movieElement = null;
6496 
6497 		// Setup global control tracking
6498 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = this;
6499 
6500 		// Load the settings.  Load the Flash movie.
6501 		this.initSettings();
6502 		this.loadFlash();
6503 		this.displayDebugInfo();
6504 	} catch (ex) {
6505 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
6506 		throw ex;
6507 	}
6508 };

6551 // Private: initSettings ensures that all the
6552 // settings are set, getting a default value if one was not assigned.
6553 SWFUpload.prototype.initSettings = function () {
6554 	this.ensureDefault = function (settingName, defaultValue) {
6555 		this.settings[settingName] = (this.settings[settingName] == undefined) ? defaultValue : this.settings[settingName];
6556 	};
6557 	
6558 	// Upload backend settings
6559 	this.ensureDefault("upload_url", "");
6560 	this.ensureDefault("file_post_name", "Filedata");
6561 	this.ensureDefault("post_params", {});
6562 	this.ensureDefault("use_query_string", false);
6563 	this.ensureDefault("requeue_on_error", false);
6564 	
6565 	// File Settings
6566 	this.ensureDefault("file_types", "*.*");
6567 	this.ensureDefault("file_types_description", "All Files");
6568 	this.ensureDefault("file_size_limit", 0);	// Default zero means "unlimited"
6569 	this.ensureDefault("file_upload_limit", 0);
6570 	this.ensureDefault("file_queue_limit", 0);
6571 
6572 	// Flash Settings
6573 	this.ensureDefault("flash_url", "swfupload.swf");
6574 	this.ensureDefault("prevent_swf_caching", true);
6575 	
6576 	// Button Settings
6577 	this.ensureDefault("button_image_url", "");
6578 	this.ensureDefault("button_width", 1);
6579 	this.ensureDefault("button_height", 1);
6580 	this.ensureDefault("button_text", "");
6581 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_style", "color: #000000; font-size: 16pt;");
6582 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_top_padding", 0);
6583 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_left_padding", 0);
6584 	this.ensureDefault("button_action", SWFUpload.BUTTON_ACTION.SELECT_FILES);
6585 	this.ensureDefault("button_disabled", false);
6586 	this.ensureDefault("button_placeholder_id", null);
6587 	
6588 	// Debug Settings
6589 	this.ensureDefault("debug", false);
6590 	this.settings.debug_enabled = this.settings.debug;	// Here to maintain v2 API
6591 	
6592 	// Event Handlers
6593 	this.settings.return_upload_start_handler = this.returnUploadStart;
6594 	this.ensureDefault("swfupload_loaded_handler", null);
6595 	this.ensureDefault("file_dialog_start_handler", null);
6596 	this.ensureDefault("file_queued_handler", null);
6597 	this.ensureDefault("file_queue_error_handler", null);
6598 	this.ensureDefault("file_dialog_complete_handler", null);
6599 	
6600 	this.ensureDefault("upload_start_handler", null);
6601 	this.ensureDefault("upload_progress_handler", null);
6602 	this.ensureDefault("upload_error_handler", null);
6603 	this.ensureDefault("upload_success_handler", null);
6604 	this.ensureDefault("upload_complete_handler", null);
6605 	
6606 	this.ensureDefault("debug_handler", function(msg) {n2i.log(msg)});
6607 
6608 	this.ensureDefault("custom_settings", {});
6609 
6610 	// Other settings
6611 	this.customSettings = this.settings.custom_settings;
6612 	
6613 	// Update the flash url if needed
6614 	if (this.settings.prevent_swf_caching) {
6615 		this.settings.flash_url = this.settings.flash_url + "?swfuploadrnd=" + Math.floor(Math.random() * 999999999);
6616 	}
6617 	
6618 	delete this.ensureDefault;
6619 };
6620 
6621 SWFUpload.prototype.loadFlash = function () {
6622 	if (this.settings.button_placeholder_id !== "") {
6623 		this.replaceWithFlash();
6624 	} else {
6625 		this.appendFlash();
6626 	}
6627 };
6628 
6629 // Private: appendFlash gets the HTML tag for the Flash
6630 // It then appends the flash to the body
6631 SWFUpload.prototype.appendFlash = function () {
6632 	var targetElement, container;
6633 
6634 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
6635 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
6636 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
6637 	}
6638 
6639 	// Get the body tag where we will be adding the flash movie
6640 	targetElement = document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0];
6641 
6642 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
6643 		throw "Could not find the 'body' element.";
6644 	}
6645 
6646 	// Append the container and load the flash
6647 	container = document.createElement("div");
6648 	container.style.width = "1px";
6649 	container.style.height = "1px";
6650 	container.style.overflow = "hidden";
6651 
6652 	targetElement.appendChild(container);
6653 	container.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
6654 };
6655 
6656 // Private: replaceWithFlash replaces the button_placeholder element with the flash movie.
6657 SWFUpload.prototype.replaceWithFlash = function () {
6658 	var targetElement, tempParent;
6659 
6660 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
6661 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
6662 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
6663 	}
6664 	// Get the element where we will be placing the flash movie
6665 	targetElement = this.settings.button_placeholder || document.getElementById(this.settings.button_placeholder_id);
6666 
6667 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
6668 		throw "Could not find the placeholder element.";
6669 	}
6670 
6671 	// Append the container and load the flash
6672 	tempParent = document.createElement("div");
6673 	tempParent.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
6674 	targetElement.parentNode.replaceChild(tempParent.firstChild, targetElement);
6675 };
6676 
6677 // Private: getFlashHTML generates the object tag needed to embed the flash in to the document
6678 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashHTML = function () {
6679 	var transparent = this.settings.button_image_url === "" ? true : false;
6680 	
6681 	// Flash Satay object syntax: http://www.alistapart.com/articles/flashsatay
6682 	return ['<object id="', this.movieName, '" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="', this.settings.flash_url, '" width="', this.settings.button_width, '" height="', this.settings.button_height, '" class="swfupload">',
6683 				'<param name="wmode" value="', transparent ? "transparent" : "window", '" />',
6684 				'<param name="movie" value="', this.settings.flash_url, '" />',
6685 				'<param name="quality" value="high" />',
6686 				'<param name="menu" value="false" />',
6687 				'<param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" />',
6688 				'<param name="flashvars" value="' + this.getFlashVars() + '" />',
6689 				'</object>'].join("");
6690 };
6691 
6692 // Private: getFlashVars builds the parameter string that will be passed
6693 // to flash in the flashvars param.
6694 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashVars = function () {
6695 	// Build a string from the post param object
6696 	var paramString = this.buildParamString();
6697 
6698 	// Build the parameter string
6699 	return ["movieName=", encodeURIComponent(this.movieName),
6700 			"&uploadURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.upload_url),
6701 			"&useQueryString=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.use_query_string),
6702 			"&requeueOnError=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.requeue_on_error),
6703 			"&params=", encodeURIComponent(paramString),
6704 			"&filePostName=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_post_name),
6705 			"&fileTypes=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types),
6706 			"&fileTypesDescription=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types_description),
6707 			"&fileSizeLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_size_limit),
6708 			"&fileUploadLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_upload_limit),
6709 			"&fileQueueLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_queue_limit),
6710 			"&debugEnabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.debug_enabled),
6711 			"&buttonImageURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_image_url),
6712 			"&buttonWidth=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_width),
6713 			"&buttonHeight=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_height),
6714 			"&buttonText=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text),
6715 			"&buttonTextTopPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_top_padding),
6716 			"&buttonTextLeftPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_left_padding),
6717 			"&buttonTextStyle=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_style),
6718 			"&buttonAction=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_action),
6719 			"&buttonDisabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_disabled)
6720 		].join("");
6721 };
6722 
6723 // Public: getMovieElement retrieves the DOM reference to the Flash element added by SWFUpload
6724 // The element is cached after the first lookup
6725 SWFUpload.prototype.getMovieElement = function () {
6726 	if (this.movieElement == undefined) {
6727 		this.movieElement = document.getElementById(this.movieName);
6728 	}
6729 
6730 	if (this.movieElement === null) {
6731 		throw "Could not find Flash element";
6732 	}
6733 	
6734 	return this.movieElement;
6735 };
6736 
6737 // Private: buildParamString takes the name/value pairs in the post_params setting object
6738 // and joins them up in to a string formatted "name=value&name=value"
6739 SWFUpload.prototype.buildParamString = function () {
6740 	var postParams = this.settings.post_params; 
6741 	var paramStringPairs = [];
6742 
6743 	if (typeof(postParams) === "object") {
6744 		for (var name in postParams) {
6745 			if (postParams.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
6746 				paramStringPairs.push(encodeURIComponent(name.toString()) + "=" + encodeURIComponent(postParams[name].toString()));
6747 			}
6748 		}
6749 	}
6750 
6751 	return paramStringPairs.join("&");
6752 };
6753 
6754 // Public: Used to remove a SWFUpload instance from the page. This method strives to remove
6755 // all references to the SWF, and other objects so memory is properly freed.
6756 // Returns true if everything was destroyed. Returns a false if a failure occurs leaving SWFUpload in an inconsistant state.
6757 SWFUpload.prototype.destroy = function () {
6758 	try {
6759 		// Make sure Flash is done before we try to remove it
6760 		this.stopUpload();
6761 		
6762 		// Remove the SWFUpload DOM nodes
6763 		var movieElement = null;
6764 		try {
6765 			movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
6766 		} catch (ex) {
6767 		}
6768 		
6769 		if (movieElement != undefined && movieElement.parentNode != undefined && typeof movieElement.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
6770 			var container = movieElement.parentNode;
6771 			if (container != undefined) {
6772 				container.removeChild(movieElement);
6773 				if (container.parentNode != undefined && typeof container.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
6774 					container.parentNode.removeChild(container);
6775 				}
6776 			}
6777 		}
6778 		
6779 		// Destroy references
6780 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = null;
6781 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
6782 
6783 		delete this.movieElement;
6784 		delete this.settings;
6785 		delete this.customSettings;
6786 		delete this.eventQueue;
6787 		delete this.movieName;
6788 		
6789 		delete window[this.movieName];
6790 		
6791 		return true;
6792 	} catch (ex1) {
6793 		return false;
6794 	}
6795 };
6796 
6797 // Public: displayDebugInfo prints out settings and configuration
6798 // information about this SWFUpload instance.
6799 // This function (and any references to it) can be deleted when placing
6800 // SWFUpload in production.
6801 SWFUpload.prototype.displayDebugInfo = function () {
6802 	this.debug(
6803 		[
6804 			"---SWFUpload Instance Info---\n",
6805 			"Version: ", SWFUpload.version, "\n",
6806 			"Movie Name: ", this.movieName, "\n",
6807 			"Settings:\n",
6808 			"\t", "upload_url:               ", this.settings.upload_url, "\n",

6850 	the maintain v2 API compatibility
6851 */
6852 // Public: (Deprecated) addSetting adds a setting value. If the value given is undefined or null then the default_value is used.
6853 SWFUpload.prototype.addSetting = function (name, value, default_value) {
6854     if (value == undefined) {
6855         return (this.settings[name] = default_value);
6856     } else {
6857         return (this.settings[name] = value);
6858 	}
6859 };

6861 // Public: (Deprecated) getSetting gets a setting. Returns an empty string if the setting was not found.
6862 SWFUpload.prototype.getSetting = function (name) {
6863     if (this.settings[name] != undefined) {
6864         return this.settings[name];
6865 	}
6866 
6867     return "";
6868 };

6872 // Private: callFlash handles function calls made to the Flash element.
6873 // Calls are made with a setTimeout for some functions to work around
6874 // bugs in the ExternalInterface library.
6875 SWFUpload.prototype.callFlash = function (functionName, argumentArray) {
6876 	argumentArray = argumentArray || [];
6877 	
6878 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
6879 	var returnValue;
6880 
6881 	if (typeof movieElement[functionName] === "function") {
6882 		// We have to go through all this if/else stuff because the Flash functions don't have apply() and only accept the exact number of arguments.
6883 		if (argumentArray.length === 0) {
6884 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName]();
6885 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 1) {
6886 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0]);
6887 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 2) {
6888 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1]);
6889 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 3) {
6890 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1], argumentArray[2]);
6891 		} else {
6892 			throw "Too many arguments";
6893 		}
6894 		
6895 		// Unescape file post param values
6896 		if (returnValue != undefined && typeof returnValue.post === "object") {
6897 			returnValue = this.unescapeFilePostParams(returnValue);
6898 		}
6899 		
6900 		return returnValue;
6901 	} else {
6902 		throw "Invalid function name: " + functionName;
6903 	}
6904 };

7116 /* *******************************
7117 	Flash Event Interfaces
7118 	These functions are used by Flash to trigger the various
7119 	events.
7120 	
7121 	All these functions a Private.
7122 	
7123 	Because the ExternalInterface library is buggy the event calls
7124 	are added to a queue and the queue then executed by a setTimeout.
7125 	This ensures that events are executed in a determinate order and that
7126 	the ExternalInterface bugs are avoided.
7127 ******************************* */
7128 
7129 SWFUpload.prototype.queueEvent = function (handlerName, argumentArray) {
7130 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
7131 	
7132 	if (argumentArray == undefined) {
7133 		argumentArray = [];
7134 	} else if (!(argumentArray instanceof Array)) {
7135 		argumentArray = [argumentArray];
7136 	}
7137 	
7138 	var self = this;
7139 	if (typeof this.settings[handlerName] === "function") {
7140 		// Queue the event
7141 		this.eventQueue.push(function () {
7142 			this.settings[handlerName].apply(this, argumentArray);
7143 		});
7144 		
7145 		// Execute the next queued event
7146 		setTimeout(function () {
7147 			self.executeNextEvent();
7148 		}, 0);
7149 		
7150 	} else if (this.settings[handlerName] !== null) {
7151 		throw "Event handler " + handlerName + " is unknown or is not a function";
7152 	}
7153 };
7154 
7155 // Private: Causes the next event in the queue to be executed.  Since events are queued using a setTimeout
7156 // we must queue them in order to garentee that they are executed in order.
7157 SWFUpload.prototype.executeNextEvent = function () {
7158 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
7159 
7160 	var  f = this.eventQueue ? this.eventQueue.shift() : null;
7161 	if (typeof(f) === "function") {
7162 		f.apply(this);
7163 	}
7164 };
7165 
7166 // Private: unescapeFileParams is part of a workaround for a flash bug where objects passed through ExternalInterface cannot have
7167 // properties that contain characters that are not valid for JavaScript identifiers. To work around this
7168 // the Flash Component escapes the parameter names and we must unescape again before passing them along.
7169 SWFUpload.prototype.unescapeFilePostParams = function (file) {
7170 	var reg = /[$]([0-9a-f]{4})/i;
7171 	var unescapedPost = {};
7172 	var uk;
7173 
7174 	if (file != undefined) {
7175 		for (var k in file.post) {
7176 			if (file.post.hasOwnProperty(k)) {
7177 				uk = k;
7178 				var match;
7179 				while ((match = reg.exec(uk)) !== null) {
7180 					uk = uk.replace(match[0], String.fromCharCode(parseInt("0x" + match[1], 16)));
7181 				}
7182 				unescapedPost[uk] = file.post[k];
7183 			}
7184 		}
7185 
7186 		file.post = unescapedPost;
7187 	}
7188 
7189 	return file;
7190 };
7191 
7192 SWFUpload.prototype.flashReady = function () {
7193 	// Check that the movie element is loaded correctly with its ExternalInterface methods defined
7194 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
7195 	if (typeof movieElement.StartUpload !== "function") {
7196 		throw "ExternalInterface methods failed to initialize.";
7197 	}
7198 
7199 	// Fix IE Flash/Form bug
7200 	if (window[this.movieName] == undefined) {
7201 		window[this.movieName] = movieElement;
7202 	}
7203 	
7204 	this.queueEvent("swfupload_loaded_handler");
7205 };

7238 SWFUpload.prototype.returnUploadStart = function (file) {
7239 	var returnValue;
7240 	if (typeof this.settings.upload_start_handler === "function") {
7241 		file = this.unescapeFilePostParams(file);
7242 		returnValue = this.settings.upload_start_handler.call(this, file);
7243 	} else if (this.settings.upload_start_handler != undefined) {
7244 		throw "upload_start_handler must be a function";
7245 	}
7246 
7247 	// Convert undefined to true so if nothing is returned from the upload_start_handler it is
7248 	// interpretted as 'true'.
7249 	if (returnValue === undefined) {
7250 		returnValue = true;
7251 	}
7252 	
7253 	returnValue = !!returnValue;
7254 	
7255 	this.callFlash("ReturnUploadStart", [returnValue]);
7256 };
